summary.name: gapminder-health-income.csv
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains information about the income, health, population, and region of various countries.

properties.description: The income of the country in US dollars.
The life expectancy of the country in years.
The region where the country is located.

goals.question: What is the distribution of income across different regions?
goals.visualization: box plot of income by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the income distribution across different regions and identify any outliers or differences in income levels.

goals.question: What is the relationship between income and health?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of income vs health
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a correlation between income and health, and if countries with higher income tend to have higher life expectancy.

goals.question: What is the distribution of population across different regions?
goals.visualization: bar chart of population by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the population distribution across different regions and identify any differences in population levels.

goals.question: What is the relationship between health and population?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of health vs population
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a correlation between population and health, and if countries with higher population tend to have lower life expectancy.

goals.question: What is the distribution of countries across different regions?
goals.visualization: pie chart of countries by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the distribution of countries across different regions and identify any regions with a higher or lower number of countries.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='income', y='health', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income and health?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.groupby('region')['population'].sum().reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='region', y='population', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="population", y="health", data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Population', ylabel='Health')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between health and population?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    regions = data.groupby('region').count().reset_index()
    regions = regions[['region', 'country']]
    regions.columns = ['Region', 'Count']
    plt.pie(regions['Count'], labels=regions['Region'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of countries across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
